---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
import CookieBanner from '../components/CookieBanner.astro';
---

<html lang="en">
<head>
    <BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
    <style>
        body {
            margin: 0;
            font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
            background: linear-gradient(120deg, #0f0c29, #302b63, #24243e);
            color: #ffffff;
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 3rem;
            background: linear-gradient(90deg, #00ffff, #ff00ff, #ffea00);
            background-size: 200% 200%;
            -webkit-background-clip: text;
            -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
            animation: gradientAnimation 5s ease infinite;
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 2rem;
        }

        @keyframes gradientAnimation {
            0% { background-position: 0% 50%; }
            50% { background-position: 100% 50%; }
            100% { background-position: 0% 50%; }
        }

        section {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 50px auto;
            padding: 30px;
            border-radius: 15px;
            background: rgba(0,0,0,0.6);
            box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(0,255,255,0.2);
            backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
        }

        h2 {
            font-size: 2rem;
            color: #00ffff;
            border-bottom: 2px solid #00ffff;
            display: inline-block;
            padding-bottom: 8px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        pre {
            background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
            color: #00ffff;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 12px;
            overflow-x: auto;
            font-size: 1rem;
            line-height: 1.5;
            margin-top: 15px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <Header />

    <main>
        <h1>Plugins Help</h1>

        <section>
            <h2>MysticalGems</h2>
            <pre>
Version: 1.0
Minecraft: Paper 1.21.7
Author: Jona Gotthardt

Description:
Magical gems with unique abilities for survival and RPG servers.

Features:
- Adds magical gems with custom powers
- Gems can be used for crafting, potions, or as special items

Installation:
1. Download MysticalGems.jar
2. Place it in /plugins
3. Restart server

License:
MIT License
            </pre>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>ExtendedInventory</h2>
            <pre>
Version: 1.0
Minecraft: Paper 1.21.7
Author: Jona Gotthardt

Description:
Adds extra inventory slots for Players via /inv.

Features:
- More inventory Slots via a 52 Slot Large GUI-Inventory
- Works on vanilla Paper/Spigot servers

Installation:
1. Download ExtendedInventory.jar
2. Place it in /plugins
3. Restart server

License:
MIT License
            </pre>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>AllMobEggs</h2>
            <pre>

**Version:** 2.3.2
**Minecraft API:** 1.21

Description:

AllMobEggs adds **spawn eggs for all standard mobs**, crafted with **custom ingredients**.  
Players can craft the eggs, while admins can edit recipes via a GUI.

Features:

- Craft spawn eggs for all players
- `/eggrecipes` shows all recipes in chat
- `/newegg` opens a GUI to edit/add eggs (Admins only)
- Placeholders for mobs without a recipe
- Ingredient selection directly in the inventory
- Config-based recipes (`config.yml`)

Commands:

| Command       | Description                                           | Permission       |
|---------------|-------------------------------------------------------|----------------|
| `/eggrecipes` | Shows all spawn egg recipes in chat                   | allmobeggs.view |
| `/newegg`     | Opens the GUI to edit/add spawn eggs                 | allmobeggs.edit |
| `/allmobeggs help` | Shows this help message with crafting instructions | allmobeggs.view |

Crafting Instructions:

1. Each spawn egg is crafted using **a regular egg** and a **mob-specific ingredient**.
2. Example ingredient mappings (default recipes):

| Mob        | Ingredient     |
|------------|----------------|
| Cow        | Raw Beef       |
| Pig        | Porkchop       |
| Sheep      | White Wool     |
| Chicken    | Feather        |
| Horse      | Saddle         |
| Wolf       | Bone           |
| Villager   | Emerald        |
| Bee        | Honeycomb      |
| Panda      | Bamboo         |
| Zombie     | Rotten Flesh   |
| Skeleton   | Arrow          |
| Creeper    | Gunpowder      |
| Spider     | String         |
| Enderman   | Ender Pearl    |
| Slime      | Slime Block    |
| Witch      | Cauldron       |

3. Crafting Pattern:

   E = Egg
   I = Ingredient

[   ] [ E ] [   ]
[   ] [ I ] [   ]
[   ] [   ] [   ]

- All players can craft these eggs **without any special permissions**.  
- Ingredients can be modified via the GUI `/newegg` (Admins only).

Permissions:

| Permission         | Description                        | Default       |
|-------------------|------------------------------------|---------------|
| allmobeggs.view     | Allows using `/eggrecipes` and help command | true          |
| allmobeggs.edit     | Allows using `/newegg` GUI         | op            |
| allmobeggs.craft    | Allows crafting all spawn eggs     | true          |

Installation:

1. Place the plugin in the `/plugins/` folder  
2. Start the server â†’ `config.yml` will be created automatically  
3. Use `/newegg`, `/eggrecipes`, or `/allmobeggs help`  
4. `README.md` is saved in the plugin folder for further reference
            </pre>
        </section>
    </main>

    <Footer />
    <CookieBanner />
</body>
</html>